*1. Project Purpose and Objectives:*  
Clearly state the purpose of your project and what you aim to achieve. For example:
- "This project is focused on developing [software/system name] to [solve a problem/improve efficiency]."

*2. Scope of the Project:*  
Define the system boundaries and the features your software will cover:
- "The project includes functionalities such as [e.g., user authentication, real-time data processing, reporting, etc.] and is built to support users in [specific tasks]."

*3. Target Audience/User Groups:*  
Identify the users of your project:
- "The system is designed for [specific groups, e.g., businesses, end-users, developers]."

*4. Functional Requirements:*  
List the primary functionalities your software provides:
- "Key functionalities include [e.g., data management, API integration, responsive design]."

*5. Non-Functional Requirements:*  
Highlight performance, scalability, security, or other technical aspects:
- "Built for high performance, scalability, and user-friendly experience with robust security measures."

*6. Tools and Technologies:*  
Include the technologies used for the development:
- "Developed using technologies such as [programming languages, frameworks, database systems, etc.]."

*7. Benefits:*  
Mention the benefits your project provides:
- "The system streamlines processes, saves time, and improves accuracy in [specific areas]."
